<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-08-05T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-08-05T00:00:00-05:00" n="1532" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1532">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 817.48.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Minister</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Managua</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-08-05">
                                    <hi rend="italic">August 5, 1912</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Owing to a partial failure of crops last year and the financial
                            exhaustion of the Republic under the Zelaya régime, there was
                            wide-spread want approaching famine throughout the country before the
                            outbreak of the present trouble. On account of existing hostilities and
                            consequent prospect of increase of this suffering, does the Department
                            think it advisable to ascertain whether the American Red Cross is
                            prepared to send on short notice supplies to be distributed to
                            non-combatants under American supervision?</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Weitzel.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>